* Basics
$ git config --global user.name phua
$ git config --global user.email phua@aleph0
** Creating a new repository
$ mkdir REPOSITORY
$ cd REPOSITORY
$ git init
$ touch README
$ git add README
$ git commit -m 'first commit'
$ git remote add origin git@github.com:phua/REPOSITORY.git
$ git push origin master
** Adding an existing repository
$ cd REPOSITORY
$ git remote add origin git@github.com:phua/REPOSITORY.git
$ git push origin master
** Forking a repository
*** Cloning
$ git clone git@github.com:USER/REPOSITORY.git
$ cd REPOSITORY
*** Remoting
$ git remote add upstream git@github.com:USER/REPOSITORY.git
$ git fetch upstream
*** Pushing
$ git origin push master
*** Pulling
$ git fetch upstream
$ git merge upstream/master

$ git pull upstream
** Branching
$ git branch BRANCH
$ git checkout BRANCH

$ git checkout -b BRANCH
* Advanced
** Purging from a repository
$ find . -type d -name ".svn" -exec git filter-branch --index-filter 'git rm -r --cached --ignore-unmatch {}' --force HEAD \;
